# Medical Report Charter — Architecture

A Flask app that extracts blood test results from PDF reports (text + OCR), consolidates them, and displays trends in a web dashboard. Deployed on Render (free tier) with Dropbox as the PDF source and GitHub as persistent cache.

## File Layout

- `config.yaml` — Single source of truth for all user-configurable data.
- `pdf_processor.py` — Three-stage processing pipeline + incremental pipeline. No hardcoded data.
- `app.py` — Flask API server with background-refresh threading.
- `dropbox_sync.py` — Downloads new PDFs from Dropbox, skips already-processed files.
- `github_sync.py` — Pushes updated CSV + synced tracker to GitHub via Contents API.
- `templates/index.html` — Dashboard HTML shell (PWA-enabled).
- `static/js/app.js` — Frontend: table, filters, Chart.js trends, pivot view.
- `static/css/style.css` — Responsive styling (mobile/tablet/desktop breakpoints).
- `static/manifest.json` — PWA manifest for mobile "Add to Home Screen".
- `static/sw.js` — Service worker for offline app shell caching.
- `Dockerfile` — Container image with tesseract-ocr + poppler-utils + gunicorn.
- `render.yaml` — Render deployment blueprint.
- `data/` — Source PDFs, named `yyyy-mm-dd_ReportName.pdf` (local dev only; not in git).
- `cache/stage3_categorized.csv` — Final processed data (committed to git for instant cold starts).
- `cache/synced_files.json` — Tracks all attempted PDF filenames to avoid re-downloading.

## Three-Stage Pipeline

Each stage reads the previous stage's output and writes its own CSV:

| Stage | Function | Input | Output | Rows |
|-------|----------|-------|--------|------|
| 1 — Extract | `run_stage1()` | PDF files | `cache/stage1_raw.csv` | All parseable lines (2400+) |
| 2 — Process | `run_stage2()` | stage1 CSV | `cache/stage2_processed.csv` | Recognized tests only (900+) |
| 3 — Categorize | `run_stage3()` | stage2 CSV | `cache/stage3_categorized.csv` | Same + `category` column |

- Stage 1: Raw PDF extraction — no name normalization, no unit conversion.
- Stage 2: Name aliases, OCR unit fixes, display normalization, value conversion.
- Stage 3: Assigns `test_categories` from config. Ready for the UI.
- `run_full_pipeline()` chains all three. `clear_cache()` removes all stage files.
- `run_incremental_pipeline()` — only processes PDFs not already in stage3. Merges new rows with existing data. Used by "Refresh Data" on Render.
- `get_processed_filenames()` — returns union of filenames from stage3 CSV and `synced_files.json`.
- API endpoints read from `stage3_categorized.csv`.

## Deployment Architecture (Render + Dropbox + GitHub)

- **Render (free tier)** hosts the Docker container with tesseract + poppler + gunicorn.
- **Dropbox (App Folder access)** stores source PDFs in `/Apps/medical-charter/`.
- **GitHub** stores the repo + `cache/stage3_categorized.csv` + `cache/synced_files.json`.
- On cold start, stage3 CSV is already in the Docker image from git — dashboard loads instantly.
- "Refresh Data" flow: Dropbox sync (new PDFs only) → incremental pipeline → push updated CSV to GitHub.
- GitHub push triggers Render auto-deploy, baking the updated CSV into the next image.
- `synced_files.json` tracks all PDFs ever attempted (including skipped/failed) so they aren't re-downloaded.

### Environment Variables (Render)

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `DROPBOX_APP_KEY` | Dropbox app credentials |
| `DROPBOX_APP_SECRET` | Dropbox app credentials |
| `DROPBOX_REFRESH_TOKEN` | Long-lived OAuth2 refresh token |
| `DROPBOX_FOLDER` | Path within Dropbox app folder (use `/` for app-folder root) |
| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | Fine-grained PAT with Contents read/write on the repo |
| `GITHUB_REPO` | `owner/repo-name` (e.g. `m-mittal/medical-charter`) |

## Key Design Decisions

- All mappings live in `config.yaml` — never hardcode in Python or JS.
- Stages 2 & 3 can be re-run without re-extracting PDFs (just delete stage2+stage3 files).
- Frontend fetches test categories from `/api/config/categories`.
- Background refresh thread uses `progress_cb` for live status updates.
- Incremental pipeline avoids reprocessing all 182+ PDFs on every refresh.
- Only `stage3_categorized.csv` and `synced_files.json` are committed to git; stage1/stage2 are intermediate and gitignored.
- PWA support: manifest + service worker allow mobile "Add to Home Screen" with standalone window.
